article.headline: Princeton beats Dartmouth 64-53
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. -- Spencer Weisz scored 16 points with six rebounds and led four players in double digits as Princeton beat Dartmouth 64-53 on Saturday night. Ben Hazel added 14 points off the bench, sinking 4 of 8 from distance for the Tigers (9-10, 2-1 Ivy League). Pete Miller had 13 points and Steven Cook 10. Miller finished out the final five minutes of the first half with a dunk, two layups and a free throw to help Princeton secure a 33-24 lead at the break. Hazel took the Tigers to a 53-36 lead by sinking a 3-pointer with 11:54 left in the second half. He hit another 3 to make it 58-45 with 5:12 to play and Princeton finished out the game with 8-of-14 shooting from the line to clinch the win. Gabas Maldunas led the Big Green (8-10, 1-3) with 12 points and three rebounds.
